    <!-- The DLF/Aquifer Implementation Guidelines for Shareable MODS Records recommend the use of at least one targetAudience element when applicable, and a controlled vocabulary when available. This element is repeatable. --><fieldset><legend><span class="legend">Target Audiences</span></legend><xf:hint><p> Use Target Audience to describe a group for which a resource is intended. </p><p> Use this field whenever there is a specific audience for a
            resource (for example, a text marked up specifically for historians). Do not limit the use of Target Audience to the intellectual level of the
            audience (as suggested by the marctarget list). </p><p> If you wish to add an authority file, or wish to add terms to the Local authority file, please
                    contact <!--contact-->. When more than one target audience is recorded, the field is repeated. </p><p> Use the authority field whenever possible
                    to indicate the controlled vocabulary used. </p><p> Do not use Target Audience to indicate audiences to whom access or use of the resource is limited;
                    include this information in the Access Condition field. </p></xf:hint>
